we want to divide the likes and dislikes in such a way that they are not in the same group.

# Approach
We are using bipartite graph to separate the inputs in two groups of likes and dislikes with two colors such that no same colors are together like we check the bipartitie graph, if two vertices of same color are adjacent then we can say that this graph is non bipartite hence cannot be separated in two groups so we can return false, else we can return true.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
o(n^2)

- Space complexity:
o(n^2 + n+1 + n)  ~ o(n^2)

