For this problem, we can view the dislike pair as the edge in the graph with node 1,2,...,N. So it can be converted to determine whether the graph can be colored with 2 colors such that no two adjacent vertices of the graph are colored with same color. 

Generally, the m Coloring Problem's solution is as following link:
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/m-coloring-problem-backtracking-5/

For m=2, the DFS solution is as following:
```
    def possibleBipartition(self, N, dislikes):
        """
        :type N: int
        :type dislikes: List[List[int]]
        :rtype: bool
        """

        def dfs(v, color):
            if colors[v] != 0:
                return colors[v] == color
            colors[v] = color
            for nei in graph[v]:
                if not dfs(nei, -color):
                    return False
            return True

        graph = [[] for _ in range(N + 1)]
        for edge in dislikes:
            if edge:
                graph[edge[0]].append(edge[1])
                graph[edge[1]].append(edge[0])

        colors = [0 for _ in range(N + 1)]
        for i in range(1, N + 1):
            if colors[i] == 0 and not dfs(i, 1):
                return False
        return True
