We can use the functional programming concept of [reduce](http://iandundas.com/blog/2016/6/14/swift-basics-reduce) to do this quickly and cleanly:

```
func subtractProductAndSum(_ n: Int) -> Int {
    // Attempts to convert every character in this string (a digit) to an int.
	// `compactMap` removes failed conversions which would return `nil`.
	// If the number is well-formatted, this shouldn't be a problem.
	let digits = String(n).compactMap { digitAsCharacter in
		Int(String(digitAsCharacter)
	}

	// Start at a value of 1 and multiply every digit to get the product.
	let product = digits.reduce(1) { x, y in x * y }

	// Start at a value of 0 and add every number to get the sum.
	let sum = digits.reduce(0) { x, y in x + y }

	return product - sum
}
```

