solutions.content:
* `sum` is the wait time of the customers
* `time` is the current time 
* `subract` is for overlap time

`time - customer[0] <= 0` means there is no overlaping so the code does `time - customer[0] > 0` and makes the overlapping time `time - customer[0]`. If no overlap then we can set `time = customer[0]` but `time += customer[0] - time`

`time += customer[1]` is for adding the chefs cook time.

`sum += customer[1] + subtract` is adding the chefs cook time with the overlap time and then adding it to the total wait time.

```
func averageWaitingTime(customers [][]int) float64 {
	time := 0
	sum := 0
	for _, customer := range customers {
		subtract := 0
		if time-customer[0] > 0 {
			subtract = time - customer[0]
		} else {
			time = customer[0]
		}
		time += customer[1]
		sum += customer[1] + subtract
	}
	return float64(sum) / float64(len(customers))
}
```

