solutions.content:
Consider variable t to be the time currently and waitingTime is the sum of all the times that each customer waits. Initially, the time will be the sum of the arrival time of the customer and the time taken for the chef to finish the order. The waitingTime will be the customer's arrival time subtracted from the time.

For the next customers, the time will be the sum of the previous time and the next customer's order preparation time. The waiting time will be similar to the initial case.

In the exceptional case that the time is less than the next customer's arrival time (the customer has not arrived yet) , then change time to accomodate it.

Basically, this is an implementation of the **FCFS scheduling algorithm in OS** where the customer's arrival time is the arrival time and the preparation time for the order is the burst time.

