# Intuition
We need to track the customers timeline, at what time customer came, if two customers timeline overlap, it means we need to extend the timeline. But if the timeline does not overlap, we start the timeline from there.
# Approach
Example: [[5,2],[5,4],[10,3],[20,1]]
Timeline starts when the first order arrive. so
timeline = 5
wait_time = 0;
First Order: while chef is preparing the order which takes 2 unit time, so 
timeline = 5 + 2
wait_time = timeline - arrival_time of order1 = 7 - 5 = 2

Second Order:
As second order arrived when first order was being prepared, so we will extend the timeline as 5 < 7, as we can't deliver the order before 7 + time to prepare order 2 which is 11. so:
timeline = 7 + 4 = 11
wait_time += timeline - arrival_time of order 2 = 11 - 5 = 6

Third Order:
Third order arrived at 10, chef is busy preparing last order yet, as its time to complete is 11. so we extend our timeline with its preparation time.
timeline = 11 + 3 = 14
wait_time = timeline - arrival_time of order3 = 14 - 10 = 4

Foruth Order:
See this order at 20 our chef would be free since 14, so chef can simply start making it because its not overlapping, and timeline starts from here we discard the old one.

timeline = arrival_time of order 4 + preparation time = 20 + 1 = 21;
wait_time = timeline - arrival_time or order 4 = 21 - 20 = 1;

so 2 + 6 + 4 + 1 = 3.25.


