# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We will solve the probem iteratively

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
-Store the first customer's totalFinishtime by adding arrival and prepare time.
-We will use an array to store all the waiting time.
-Start from index 1 to length-1.
-if the arrival time is greater than current totalFinishtime we will change totalFinishtime to addition of arrival and preperation time.
-else we will update the totalFinishtime by adding prepareTime to it.
-Now we will calculate the waiting time which is substraction of totalFinishtime and arrival time.
-Store the new waiting time to an array.
-Lastly return the average of elements in an array.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
