# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We attend to each customer as they enter in, ```time += customers[i][1];```
please bear in mind the time they enter maybe greater then the total time we have spent so far. Hence we handle that.
```
if(customers[i][0] + customers[i][1] > time)
        time = customers[i][0] + customers[i][1];
```
Then we add up the waiting time for that customer ```waitingTime += (time - customers[i][0]);``` Then take the average at the end.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:** O(n)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: **O(n)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    double averageWaitingTime(vector<vector<int>>& customers) {
        int n = customers.size();
        long long time = customers[0][0], waitingTime = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i<n; i++)
        {
            time += customers[i][1];
            if(customers[i][0] + customers[i][1] > time)
                time = customers[i][0] + customers[i][1];
            waitingTime += (time - customers[i][0]);
        }
        return static_cast<double>(waitingTime)/n;
    }
};
```
